{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"The real delimiter bug is in `parseSitesFixesConfig` and `indexSitesFixesConfig`: they treat any line of `==` as a record separator, which collides with wrapped Base64 padding inside a CSS command. I’m going to replace the delimiter scan with a small stateful splitter that ignores delimiter-looking lines while inside `CSS`."}}
